Croatia Sold Euros to Support Kuna Today, Central Bank Says

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-09-19T14:04:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/croatia-sold-euros-to-support-kuna-today-central-bank-says.html
The Croatian central bank sold
180.5 million euros ($246 million) and bought kuna today on the
foreign-exchange market to support its currency, the bank said
today in an e-mailed statement.  The bank also called an extraordinary session tomorrow to
discuss changes in obligatory reserves of commercial banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Douglas Lytle at 
 dlytle@bloomberg.net  